Updated [prob.in.qm.md](/home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive/content/papers/prob.in.qm.md).

Concise summary of changes:
- Added minimal equation-numbering tags (`\tag{...}`) to display equations referenced in prose: `(1)`, `(2a)`, `(2b)`, `(3)`, `(5)`, `(8)`, `(10)`, `(11)`–`(19)`, `(23)`, `(24)`, `(29)`, `(30)`, `(32)`.
- Split dense prose blocks with blank-line paragraph boundaries (double newlines) in major text-wall regions for cleaner Hugo markdown rendering.
- Fixed footnote citation placement by moving stray standalone markers into proper inline positions (`[^2][^3]`, `[^4]`, `[^5]`, `[^6]`).
- Removed extraneous metadata-style footnote `[^1]` (“revised and extended version...”), which was not part of the paper body.
- Kept paper meaning and all mathematical expressions/content unchanged (only structural/numbering markup adjustments).  
- Self-check passed: no standalone dangling footnote markers and all in-text equation references now map to visible numbered display equations.
